The paper deals with the problem of revenue maximization in social networks, which is a topic that falls under game theory (cs.GT) and social networks (cs.SI). The use of algorithms to compute equilibria and optimize pricing strategies suggests a focus on computational complexity (cs.DS) and optimization (cs.MA). The mention of a common distribution and uniform distribution also suggests a possible connection to information theory (cs.IT).
